<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="COL" stage="Final" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="John Wimbish" created="2009-10-05 05:53:30Z" when="2009-10-05 05:53:30Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Lazarus Aplugi; keyboarded by Helena Aplugi; team revision Maret 08; with advisor Aug 22 08 in Kupang; UNS in Ndao 30 Aug 08 w/Chuck &amp; team; Consultant check with Dave Glasgow in Kupang, 9 Oct 2008</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Kolose</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Sasuri Paulus<bt>Paulus' letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">hia dhèu parcaya ètu kota<bt>to the believers (believing people) in the city of</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Kolose<bt>Kolose</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii maho'o nèti Paulus si<bt>Greetings from Paulus mob</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Lii maho'o nèti ja'a, Paulus. Ama Lamatua mesa Na ka dhu hag'e nare ja'a, ho j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha Yesus Kristus. Ètu ne'e, abhu kahèi a'ari èdhi Timotius dhu pa'adhu lii maho'o hia miu.<bt>Greetings from me, Paulus. God himself is the one who chose me to become Yesus Kristus' *apostle (=emissary, one sent w/mission, comission). Here there is also our-inc sibling Timotius who sends greetings to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Paul, apostle of Christ Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Paul, apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God and Timothy the brother,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ja'a suri sasuri ne hia miu, dhèu unu Ama Lamatua ètu kota Kolose, dhu tao madhutu taruu j'ara mamuri Yesus Kristus.<bt>I write this letter to you-pl, God's people in the city of Kolose, who continue to follow/obey Yesus Kristus' way of life (lifestyle, character, values).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ji'i manèngi sèna ka Ama èdhi, Ama Lamatua, pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi miu aa'i-aa'i mi, ho miu mamuri dènge mera-milu.<bt>We-exc ask that God, our-inc Father, show His goodness/grace/kindness to you, so that you can live in safety/security (situational), and peace (relational) (doublet). [EXEG: word study on /eirene/ and formula we use for Paul's greetings.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: to the saints and faithful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: to the saints and faithful brothers in Christ in Colossae, grace to you and peace from God our Father.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus sabaj'a hia dhèu parcaya ètu Kolose<bt>Paulus prays for the believers in Kolose</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Lod'o-lod'o dhu ji'i sabaj'a hia miu, ji'i manèngi makasi mi Ama Lamatua dhu j'aj'i Ama nèti Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>Each time we-exc here pray for you, we give thanks to God, who is Father of our-inc Head, Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We always thank God the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We always thank God the Father and our Lord Jesus Christ when we pray for you,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te ji'i tadèngi ae le, nèti parcaya miu mi Yesus Kristus, aa nèti sasue dènge d'ara hua iia miu mi dhèu parcaya aa'i-aa'i.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we have heard many things about your faith/belief/trust in Yesus Kristus, and about your love/pity and goodness/kindness/generosity toward all believers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because we have heard of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because we have heard of your faith in Christ Jesus and the love which you have for all the saints,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Miu tao sèmi èèna, lula miu me'a mèu madha j'ara dhu be'a dhu tao tèke le hia miu ètu sorga. J'ara-j'ara sèra, miu tadèngi mèdhi le nèti lii holo-nori dhu lèke, nuka Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua,<bt>You do that, because you know clearly that there are good things which are stored-away for you in heaven. These things, you have heard from the true words/message/sayings, that is God2's Good News,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="elpidos: hope, expectation, something hoped for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">elpidos: hope, expectation, something hoped for apokeimai: be put away, stored up, laid up, reserved<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: because of the hope stored up for you in heaven. Of this you have heard before in the word of truth, the Good News.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />dhu dhèu peka le dènge miu karèi nèti uru ka. Lii Lolo Be'a ne, pale-lème le buli mia-mia ètu rai-haha ne, aa abhu hua-hela dhu be'a, lula lii ne ub'a mamuri dhèu j'aj'i be'a. Mamuri miu j'aj'i be'a sèmi èèna kahèi, karèi nèti hiu-hiu èèna miu tadèngi Lii Lolo Be'a, dènge me'a mèu d'ara hua iia Ama Lamatua.<bt>which people have gone to tell/explain to you from previously. That Good News has already spread everywhere/all over this world, and has gotten good results/produced good fruits, because that message/voice changes people's lives to become good. Your lives have also become good like that, beginning from the very first time you heard that Good News, and truly understood God's goodness/grace/kindness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareimi: be present, come and stay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">pareimi: be present, come and stay karpophorew: bear fruit, change people's conduct and character<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>auksanw: grow, increase, extend its influence epiginwskw: know, understand<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: It has come to you, just as also in the whole world it is producing fruit and growing, so also among you, from the day you heard and understood the grace of God in truth.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Miu se abhu le a'aj'a ne'e nèti Epapras, angalai d'ara sasab'a ji'i dhu ji'i sue. Te nèngu maj'èni pakako taruu sasab'a Yesus ètu talora aae miu.<bt>You have learned these teachings from elder.brother Epafras, our fellow worker whom we love. Cuz (elaboration) he is diligent/industrious to keep carrying out Kristus' work among you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You learned it from Epaphras"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You learned it from Epaphras our dear fellow servant, who is a faithful servant of Christ for you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 4:12, Pilmon 23</note><v n="8" />Na lolo hia ji'i ètu ne'e lula-nèti sasue miu dhu Roh Lamatua pala-bagi hia miu.<bt>He has been telling/reporting to us here about your love/pity, which God2's Spirit has given you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="delow: reveal, make clear LITERALLY: He"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">delow: reveal, make clear LITERALLY: He revealed to us your love in the spirit.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Nèti èèna ka, karèi nèti lod'o hiu-hiu ji'i tadèngi j'ara mamuri miu, ji'i loe boe sabaj'a hia miu. Ji'i manèngi Ama Lamatua, ho miu bisa me'a mèu dad'èi Na, aa bisa me'a madha j'ara ae-ae, madhutu ngaa dhu Roh Na aj'a miu.<bt>Because of that, beginning from the first time we heard about your-pl lives, we have not ceased to pray for you. We ask God that you can truly know His will, and you can understand many things, according to what it is that God2's Spirit teaches you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because of this we also,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because of this we also, from the day we heard, do not stop praying for you and asking that you may be filled with the knowledge of his will in all spiritual wisdom and understanding.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Dènge j'ara ne'e, miu bisa mamuri dhu lèke, dènge mèti kolongara hua iia Ama Lamatua. Aa miu bisa pakarej'e d'ara Lamatua ètu madha j'ara aa'i-aa'i ra kahèi. Ladhe miu pad'elo d'ara be'a mi dhèu, pe Lamatua hia miu hua-hela dhu be'a. Dènge sèmi èèna, miu asa tadhe mèu Lamatua.<bt>In that way, you can live right/ appropriately, and bear God's good name/reputation. And you can also make God2's insides happy in all matters. If you show your goodness/kindness to people, then God2 will give you good results. In that way, you can increasingly know God2 more deeply.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paj'uj'u = tunju = padelo [UNS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">paj'uj'u = tunju = padelo [UNS prefer this]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: [We pray that you may]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: [We pray that you may] live worthy of the Lord, pleasing him in everything, bearing fruit in every good work, and increasing in the knowledge of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11-13" />Ji'i manèngi-mangaj'i kahèi mi Ama Lamatua, sèna ka Nèngu hia miu koasa Na dhu dedha risi èèna, ho miu bisa tago j'ara aa'i-aa'i ra dènge taha d'ara. Ji'i manèngi ho d'ara miu dènge karej'e-karae, sèna ka miu manèngi makasi taruu mi Ama Lamatua. Te Na bhoke le j'ara, sèna ka miu sèmi mere pusaka pala miu ètu sorga. Pusaka èèna ka dhu Na pala-bagi mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra dhu parcaya Yesus Kristus. Te Na patabuli eele le èdhi nèti koasa maroga, hèia Na pamaso èdhi j'aj'i dhèu unu Yesus Kristus sèna ka pea ètu d'ara saraa. Ama Lamatua ka dhu ded'e Yesus Kristus j'aj'i Dhèu Aae èdhi. Yesus ne, Ana Pasue Ama Lamatua.<bt>We also pray asking God to give His high power/authority so you can bear/carry/endure all things with patience. We ask that your insides can be full of happiness, so you will continually give thanks to Father God. Cuz (elaboration) He has opened the way so you can receive (your) portion of inheritance in heaven. That inheritance, He gives to all people who believe in Yesus Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) He has already freed/released us-inc from the powers of darkness [yes, they use this phrase all the time; associated with evil spirits], and entered us into becoming Yesus Kristus' people, to live in the light. God has also elevated/appointed Yesus Kristus, to be/become our-inc King. That Yesus, is God's beloved Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Verses coalesced because the &quot;light&quot; metaphor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">Verses coalesced because the "light" metaphor doesn't mean anything. Light and darkness are interpreted here as moral, because we're implied to have been "under the power of darkness," so it's probably not the understanding reading. LITERALLY: [That you may] be strengthened with all power according to his glorious might for all endurance and patience.<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: With joy thank the Father, who has made us able to share the inheritance of the saints in light. LITERALLY: He rescued us from the power of darkness and transferred us into the kingdom of his beloved Son.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te Ama Lamatua hia Ana Na, sèna ka sui nare èdhi, dènge saku eele sasala-sasigo èdhi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God has turned-over/surrendered/given up that Child of His, to (fully) *redeem us and wipe away our-inc wrongs (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;let us guys go?&quot; 2:13, 3:13"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">"let us guys go?" 2:13, 3:13 NOT HERE. "pay the price" covers that component of forgiveness, so "let go" would be overkill. LITERALLY: In Christ we have redemption, the forgiveness of sins.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="soro = sorong, but UNSs prefer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">soro = sorong, but UNSs prefer hia</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 1:7</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus ne, dedha risi aa'i<bt>That Kristus, is highest of all</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Kristus ne, ca ropa dènge Ama Lamatua,<bt>That Kristus, is the same model/type/form as God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dhu dhèu rai-haha bisa boe ladhe rèdhi.<bt>who humans cannot see.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèngu dhu mema le, uru nèti aa'i-aa'i,<bt>He already was/existed before everything (else),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa Nèngu j'aj'i Kètu nèti aa'i-aa'i dhu Ama Lamatua paj'aj'i.<bt>and He is Head of everything that God has created.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He is the image of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn of all creation,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Te Ama Lamatua pake Ne,<bt>Cuz (backgrounded reason) God used Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ho paj'aj'i aa'i isi nèti dedha-liru dènge rai-haha.<bt>to create all the contents of heaven and earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Na paj'aj'i j'ara-j'ara dhu dhèu rai-haha bisa ladhe rèdhi,<bt>He made/created things that humans can see,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dènge dhu bisa boe ladhe rèdhi.<bt>and that humans cannot see.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Nuka, rèngu dhu rèd'u paredha, rèngu dhu rèd'u koasa,<bt>For example, those who hold rule/government, those who hold power/authority,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dhèu aae-dhèu aae, dènge dhèu kapai-dhèu kapai sèra.<bt>kings, and leaders.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Aa'i-aa'i dhu Ama Lamatua neo tao sèra,<bt>Everything that God wants to do/make,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Na tao hia mi Yesus Kristus,<bt>He did/made for Yesus Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">aa Yesus dhu sab'a sèra aa'i-aa'i kahèi.<bt>and Yesus is also the one who did all that work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="List of terms matched with Eph"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">List of terms matched with Eph 1:21. LITERALLY: because in him all things in heaven and earth were created, visible and invisible, whether thrones or lords or rulers or powers/authorities; all things were created by him and for him.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Lod'o aa'i-aa'i se dhae j'aj'i mèka,<bt>When everything else did not yet exist,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te Nèngu ka dhu mema-mema le.<bt>nevertheless He already existed beforehand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Aa'i-aa'i se pa'èki dènge Ne.<bt>All these things are bound/joined to Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aa Nèngu ka dhu uri si.<bt>And He is the one who arranges/regulates them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He is before all things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He is before all things and all things hold together in him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Nèngu ka dhu j'aj'i Kètu mi dhèu parcaya aa'i-aa'i.<bt>He is the one who is Head of all believers,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kephale: head = source"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">kephale: head = source</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aa dhèu parcaya sèra, nuka sèmi ngi'u Na.<bt>And believers are like His body.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Nèngu ka dhu pakako aa'i-aa'i si.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who carries out/sets in motion everything.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèti aa'i-aa'i dhu madhe, hèia mamuri hari,<bt>From/among everything/everyone that dies and then lives again,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nèngu ka dhu kapai risi,<bt>He is the most important/greatest,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ho sèna ka Nèngu ka dhu dedha risi aa'i mèu-mèu.<bt>so that He is the highest of/over all (Maximum degree).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He is the head of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He is the head of the body, the church. He is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, that he may be first in everything.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 1:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="19" />Aa'i-aa'i dhu ètu d'ara Ama Lamatua,<bt>Everything which is in God's Being/Self,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">abhu kahèi ètu d'ara Kristus,<bt>is also found/exists in Kristus' Being/Self.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">aa èèna ka dhu pakarej'e d'ara Lamatua.<bt>and that makes God2 happy,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because in him [God] was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because in him [God] was pleased to have all the fullness dwell.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="20" />Ama Lamatua pake Yesus Kristus,<bt>God used Yesus Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ho padame dènge aa'i-aa'i dhu Na paj'aj'i le.<bt>to bring relational-peace/reconciliation with everything that He has created.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Na hia Ana Na,<bt>He gave His Child,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ho j'aj'i korban dhu pasuti raa Na,<bt>to be a sacrifice which spilled His blood,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa madhe ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha,<bt>and died on a *cross,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sèna ka aa'i-aa'i ètu dedha-liru,<bt>so that everything that exists in heaven,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">aa aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne,<bt>and everything on earth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">bisa padame hari dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>can be reconciled/at peace again with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and through him to reconcile"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and through him to reconcile all things to himself, making peace through the blood of his cross, whether things on earth or things in heaven.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Uru èèna, miu mamuri ètu li'u, pakaj'èu nèti Ama Lamatua. Miu pamusu dènge Ne, ka mamuri pacèri nèti Nèngu, lula d'ara miu karehe dènge tatao dhu bhelu èèna ka, miu lab'a taruu Ne.<bt>Formerly, you lived on the outside, far/distanced from God. You were enemies/opposing Him, and so lived separated from Him, because your rotten insides (scheming/plotting/evil intent) and your evil deeds, were opposing/rebelling against Him continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Once you were alienated and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Once you were alienated and enemies in your minds by your evil deeds,</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa limuri ne Nèngu ka dhu bhoke le j'ara, ho èdhi bisa padame hari dènge Ne. Te Nèngu ka dhu pua Ana Na, ho j'aj'i dhèu rai-haha. Aa Nèngu ka dhu hia Ana Na èèna j'aj'i mi korban, aa madhe ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha, sèna ka èdhi bisa padame hari dènge Ne. Yesus Kristus tao j'ara ne'e, ho bisa lere nèti èdhi lati titu ètu katanga madha Ama Lamatua, sèna ka j'aj'i dhèu mola-mèci dènge d'ara mola, dhu dènge heka sasala ngaa-ngaa.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless now He is the one who has opened the way so we-inc can be reconciled/relational peace with Him again. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who sent/commissioned His Child to become a human. And He is the one who allowed that Child of His to become a sacrifice, and die on the cross so we could be reconciled with Him again. Yesus Kristus does that, so He can escort us to go stand before God, to be clean/holy/pure people, with straight/right/honest insides, who have no wrong anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: but now he has reconciled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: but now he has reconciled you by Christ's physical body through death, to present you holy in his sight, blameless and without accusation,</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Sad'i miu taha taruu dènge lalèka miu. Kèpe pa'èra-èra, sèna ka baku kalau! Baku pakaj'èu nèti Lii Lolo Be'a èèna, dhu miu sèmi mere ropa miu nanene hiu-hiu Lii èèna. Te Lii Lolo Be'a èèna j'aj'i mi era sarai miu. Dhèu lasi palolo lème le Lii Lolo Be'a èèna ètu mia-mia ètu rai-haha ne. Aa Lamatua ka pua ja'a, Paulus, sèna ka laku lole Lii Lolo Be'a ne kahèi.<bt>The important thing is, you-pl must keep enduring/persevering in your faith/belief/trust. Hold firm so you don't be shaken/moved/waver! Do not retreat/shy away from that Good News, which you received the first time you heard it. Cuz (elaboration) that Good News is like your place of leaning/depending. People have gone to tell that Good News all over the world. And God2 has commissioned me, Paulus, so I also go tell that Good News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sarai = sandar, lean on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">sarai = sandar, lean on</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: provided you continuue in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: provided you continuue in the faith, stable and steadfast, not shifting from the hope of the Good News which you heard, which has been preached to every creature under heaven, of which I, Paul, became aa minister/servant.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus sab'a sèna ka ladhe-leru dhèu unu Lamatua<bt>Paulus works to serve God2's people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Lod'o Kristus mamuri ètu rai-haha ne, Na dui j'aj'èra ae d'ai seli. Aa limuri ne, ja'a pasae rupa-rupa j'aj'èra kahèi. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa d'ara ja'a karej'e taruu. Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu hud'i abhu ku j'aj'èra, na, hud'i laa ja'a dui j'aj'èra èèna sama-sama dènge ra, nuka sèmi Kristus pasae nare j'aj'èra nèti dhèu-dhèu unu Na. Te dhèu unu Na, j'aj'i sama sèmi ngi'u Nèngu.<bt>[Follows Hawaii-HCE] When Kristus lived on this earth, He got/experienced great suffering/difficulty. And now I am also bearing various sorts of difficulty. Even that being the case, nevertheless my insides continue to be happy. If there is someone who must experience suffering, just let me be the one to bear that suffering with them, just like Kristus bore sufferings of His people. Cuz (elaboration) His people are like His body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now I rejoice in sufferings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now I rejoice in sufferings for you, and I complete that which is lacking in my flesh/body of the afflictions of Christ, for his body's sake, which is the church.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ama Lamatua hia ja'a sasab'a Na kahèi, ho ladhe-leru dhèu-dhèu unu Na. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a aj'a Lii Holo-Nori Na, toke lutu-sela hia miu.<bt>God has given me work-responsibility to serve His people. That is why I teach His Words/Sayings to you in fine detail.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have become its servant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have become its servant by the assignment God gave me to fully present to you the word of God,</Message></Annotation><v n="26-27" />Dhèu tadèngi Lii Holo-Nori Lamatua karèi nèti uru ka. Te ngaa dhae re'a mèu mèka naneo nèti Lii Holo-Nori se'e dènge be'a, te naneo na dhu pahuni era. Te ngaa limuri ne, Lamatua bhoke le naneo ne hia dhèu unu Na. Aa naneo Na èèna, lii dhu kapai titu kèna pala mi suku aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne. Lii babe'a dhu kapai risi èèna, nuka:<bt>From the beginning, people heard God2's Words/Sayings/Message. But they did not yet understand the purpose/intention of that Words/Sayings/Message clearly, cuz (elaboration) that purpose was still hidden. But now, God2 has decided to open/reveal that purpose to His people. [NOTE: Gk /mysterion/ “mystery which has been revealed” resonates nicely with KM /maksud/ “purpose/intention” in the sense that it is clear to the Actor, but can be hidden, unclear, and revealed, or made clear to others.] And that purpose of His, is news which is absolutely amazing/incredible for every tribe &amp; ethnic group on the earth. That incredible news, is:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kristus mamuri ètu d'ara miu!<bt>Kristus is living in your insides!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Èèna na ka dhu tao miu parcaya taruu, peka na,<bt>It is that which makes you continue to believe, that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">bèli-camèd'a Nèngu tao j'ara dhu hua iia risi hia miu ètu sorga.<bt>He will do the best things for you in heaven.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ne'e ne ka dhu èdhi dhèu rai-haha ne mate tae-tae karèi nèti uru-uru j'ara ka.<bt>It is this which we humans have been waiting/hoping for from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: the secret that has been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: the secret that has been kept hidden for ages and from generations, but is now shown to the saints. LITERALLY: To them among the Gentiles God has chosen to make known the glorious riches of this secret, which is Christ in you, the hope of glory.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />De ji'i peka dènge dhèu aa'i-aa'i lula-nèti Kristus. Ji'i aj'a-nori dènge pasanèd'e dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra, pake ngangee lii padhai dhu Ama Lamatua hia mi ji'i. Ji'i tao j'ara se'e, ho pa'èra dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu madhutu Kristus, sèna ka bèli-camèd'a rèngu bisa titu ètu madha Na, dhu dènge boe makae, lula ra mamuri mola taruu.<bt>So, we tell/explain to everyone about Kristus. We teach and warn/remind everyone, using every idea/reason/tactic that God gives to us. We do this, to strengthen/encourage/equip everyone who believes in Kristus. so that later they can stand before Him without shame, because they continue to live straight/correct/right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nouthetountes: &quot;tell dem how dey gotta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">nouthetountes: "tell dem how dey gotta make", contextual adaptation from all other usages.* LITERALLY: We preach him, counseling/warning every person and teaching every person with all wisdom, so that we may present every person perfect/mature in Christ.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Nèti èèna ka, ja'a titu pa'èra, aa sab'a j'èra titu kèna hia miu. Ja'a bisa taha sab'a bia sèmi èèna, lula koasa Kristus ka pa'èra ja'a. Aa koasa Na èèna, kapai titu kèna!<bt>That is why I stand firm/strong and work extra hard (Idiom: work with great suffering) for you-pl. I can persevere working hard like that, because Kristus' power/authority is what gives me strength. And that power/authority of His, is absolutely great/ amazing/ incredible!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For this I labor, struggling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For this I labor, struggling with the energy he powerfully works/activates in me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Miu dhu pea ètu kota Kolose, aa miu ètu kota Laodikia, dènge rèngu dhu paraga rèdhi mèka dènge ja'a. Nanene paie-iie! Ja'a d'èi sèna ka miu aa'i-aa'i mi me'a mèu sasab'a ja'a dhu bia ne hia miu, aa hia mi rèngu kahèi.<bt>You who live in the city of Kolose, and2 those in the city of Laodikia, and those who have never yet met me! Listen up! I want for everyone to know of my hard work for you-pl, and for them as well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ja'a dèi sèna ka miu aa'i-aa'i"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">Ja'a dèi sèna ka miu aa'i-aa'i mi me'a mèu sasaba ja'a dhu bia ne hia miu, aa hia mi rèngu dhu pea ètu kota Kolose, kota Laodikia dènge dhu dhae tadhe mèka ja'a.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="helikos: how great agwn: struggle, fight,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">helikos: how great agwn: struggle, fight, conflict, inward conflict, anxiety, earnest concern, care, prayer<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: For I want you to how great is my anxiety/struggle for you, and for those in Laodicea, and for as many as have not seen me face to face,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dad'èi ja'a ka, neo pa'èra d'ara rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra, sèna ka rèngu bisa pa'èki j'aj'i mi èci, lula ra mamuri pasue. Hèia ra j'aj'i re'a mèu, lula rèngu re'a tare'a, na, uru èèna naneo Lamatua pahuni era. Dhu pahuni èèna, nuka Kristus!<bt>My purpose is to strengthen/encourage all of their insides, so they can also be bound/joined becoming one/united because they are living in mutual love. So they come to know clearly, because they truly understand that previously God2's purpose was still hidden. What was hidden, is Kristus!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakalew: comfort, strengthen, encourage sumbibazw: unite,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">parakalew: comfort, strengthen, encourage sumbibazw: unite, knit together, bind together<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>ploutos: riches, wealth plerophoria: certainty, assurance<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>sunesis: insight, understanding epignwsis: knowledge<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>musterion: secret, mystery, something hidden LITERALLY: that their hearts may be encouraged, as they are knit together in love, to have the [riches of assured understanding / full assurance of understanding], for the knowledge of God's mystery, of Christ,<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ladhe miu pa'èki j'aj'i d'ara èci dènge Kristus, heka Na hia miu d'èlu-mèu dhu miu parluu, aa aj'a miu pake mamèu se, sèna ka tao j'ara-j'ara dhu be'a. Mamèu se'e se, nuka sèmi mèdha-panyau dhu kab'ua.<bt>If you are bound/joined becoming one insides (in accord, in harmony, same purpose) with Kristus, only then will He give you every cleverness/understanding/wisdom that you need, and teach you to use these understanding/wisdom to do things that are good. This cleverness/understanding/wisdom is like an expensive heirloom.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thesauros: treasure sophia: wisdom [general, larger,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">thesauros: treasure sophia: wisdom [general, larger, higher], power of reasoning about truths and applying them to life<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>gnwsis: knowledge [specific], understanding of truths apokruphos: hidden, concealed<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: in whom are all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge hidden.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ja'a peka dènge miu j'ara se aa'i-aa'i, sèna ka mage dhoka dhèu mai kapod'e-kabèli miu dènge hèb'a mènyi.<bt>I tell/explain to you all these things, so that there is nobody who can come and deceive/trick you with an oily mouth (=smooth talking).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ag'o = tipu [UNSs not know]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">ag'o = tipu [UNSs not know]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paralogizomai: be deceived, be deluded, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">paralogizomai: be deceived, be deluded, be fooled, be led atray pithanologia: persuasive speech, beguiling words, enticing words, false arguments, fine sounding arguments, attractive arguments<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: I say this in order that none of you may be fooled with persuasive words.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ja'a mema kaj'èu nèti miu. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa ja'a bhèlu boe miu, lula d'ara ja'a dhu pa'èki le dènge miu. Aa ja'a karej'e, lula ke'a, na, miu mamuri dhu lèke, aa miu dhu kèpe pa'èra parcaya miu mi Kristus era.<bt>It is true that I am far from you. Even that being the case, nevertheless I do not forget you, because my insides are bound/linked to you. And I am happy, because I know that you are living right/appropriately, and you continue to hold strongly to your faith in Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maho'o = karej'e [but UNSs not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">maho'o = karej'e [but UNSs not know]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeimi: absent xaipw: rejoice, be glad,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">apeimi: absent xaipw: rejoice, be glad, have joy<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>taksis: fixed order, order, orderly arrangement [military metaphor] sterewma: firmness, solid, steadfastness, stability<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pneumati: with you in Spirit, cf. 1 Cor 5:3 "No matta I no stay dea wit you guys, my heart stay dea." ;"even if" = relationship close; "no matta" = relationship not affected, = neva mind DM.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: For though absent in body, I am with you in spirit, rejoicing to see your good order and the firmness of your faith in Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èdhi dhu pa'èki dènge Kristus, unu mamuri dhu lèke<bt>We who are bound/joined with Kristus, get true/real life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Lula uru èèna miu sèmi mere le Yesus Kristus j'aj'i Kètu miu, nèti èèna ka limuri ne, miu hud'i nanene Ne taruu. Aa Nèngu èèna j'aj'i Kètu miu era.<bt>Because formerly you have received/accepted Yesus Kristus as your Head, that is why now, you must continue to listen to/obey Him. Cuz (elaboration) He is still your Head.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As therefore you received Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As therefore you received Christ Jesus the Lord, live in him,</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ladhe miu pa'èki taruu dènge Ne sèmi èèna, miu nuka sèmi ana aaj'u dhu asa tabha èra, lula amo la'e asa marèma aae. Aa miu nuka sèmi èmu dhu èra, lula dhu patitu ètu fanderen dhu èra. Miu pa'èra taruu ètu d'ara lalèka miu, sama sèmi a'aj'a dhu miu abhu mèdhi le. Hud'i laa, sèna ka d'ara miu pasoa-pasoka ètu d'ara manèngi makasi, lula j'ara aa'i-aa'i ra dhu Ama Lamatua tao tèke le hia miu.<bt>If you-pl live bound/joined continually to Him like that, you are like a tree which keeps growing stronger, because its roots go in buried/planted deep. And you are like a strong house, because it is built on top of a strong foundation. You keep gaining strength in your faith, just like the teaching you once got. May your insides abound/leap (doublet) with gratitude, because of everything that God has done for you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rizow: cause to take root, fix"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">rizow: cause to take root, fix firmly epoikodomew: build onto something<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>bebaiow: establish, strengthen, confirm perisseuw: be abundant, overflow, be outstanding, excel<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: rooted and built up in him, and established in the faith, just as you were taught, abounding in thanksgiving.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />J'aga paie-iie, sèna ka baku madhutu dhèu leo dhu pake d'èlu-mèu dhèu rai-haha, ho ère rèti miu nèti j'ara mola. Aa mage madhutu a'aj'a dhèu rai-haha dhu dènge boe kolo-kapua. Te a'aj'a rèngu sèra dhoka mai nèti d'èlu-mèu dhèu rai-haha di, aa nèti atora-atora rai-haha ne. Te ngaa a'aj'a sèra mai boe nèti Kristus.<bt>Be careful that you do not follow/obey other people who use human ideas/tactics/wisdom, to lead you off-path away from the straight path. And don't follow humans' teaching that is unfounded (Idiom: without tip-base). Cuz (elaboration) their teaching, just comes from human ideas/wisdom, and from the regulations/principles of this world. But those teachings do not come from Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="piku = serong [UNSs not know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">piku = serong [UNSs not know well and didn't feel it fit here] ; piru = turn s.t. like a car or a boat, but not human</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="blepw: watch, look, see sulagwgew: carry"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">blepw: watch, look, see sulagwgew: carry off as booty or captive, plunder<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>philosophia: philosophy [false teaching] kenos: empty, vain, futile, useless<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>apate: deceit, deception paradosis: tradition<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>stoixeion: fundamental principles, basic principles LITERALLY: See to it that no one takes you captive by human philosophy and empty deceit, according to human tradition, according to the basic principles of the universe, and not according to Christ.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Aa'i-aa'i dhu ètu d'ara Ama Lamatua, abhu kahèi ètu d'ara Kristus. Aa Kristus kahèi j'aj'i dhèu rai-haha, èci èèna ka dènge èdhi.<bt>Everything that exists in God's Being/Self, also exists in Kristus' Being/Self. And Kristus is also human, just like us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katoikew: dwell, live, inhabit, settle down"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">katoikew: dwell, live, inhabit, settle down plerwma: fullness, that which fills, full measure<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>theotes: deity, Godhead swmatikws: bodily, corporeally, assume a bodily form, become incarnate<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: For in him the whole fulness of deity dwells bodily.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Lula miu pa'èki le dènge Kristus, aa j'aj'i dhèu unu Na, nèti èèna ka, Na tao pamèci miu. Te Nèngu dedha risi eele nèti koasa aa'i-aa'i dènge aa'i-aa'i dhu rèd'u paredha, masi ka dhu be'a do dhu bhelu.<bt>Because you are bound to Kristus, and have become His people, that is why He is/has made you to be complete. Cuz (elaboration) He is higher than all power/authority and all that hold rule/government, whether good or evil. [Gk /kephalei/ not = Dhao /kètu/ here to avoid saying that Kristus is Head of evil spirits]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plerow: make full, fill [with powers,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">plerow: make full, fill [with powers, qualities, etc.], complete kephale: head, leader<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>arche: ruler, authority exousia: power, bearer of authority, ruler<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: And you have been made full/complete in him, who is the head of all rule and authority.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Lod'o suna dhèu Yahudi, ra j'ue eele ka'uri dhu karisi nèti era makae ra, sèna ka j'aj'i tadha, na, rèngu j'aj'i dhèu unu Ama Lamatua. Lod'o miu maso j'aj'i dhèu unu Kristus, miu suna kahèi. Sasoa na sèmi ne'e ka: suna ne, lula boe nèti dhèu j'ue eele ka'uri nèti ngi'u aae ne, te ngaa Kristus j'ue eele j'ara-j'ara bhabhelu-katub'a nèti d'ara èdhi. Nuka j'ara-j'ara bhabhelu dhu èdhi d'èi ad'u-ue, lula èdhi dhèu rai-haha.<bt>When circumcised, the Yahudi people slicing off the excess skin of their shameful place (polite euphemism for genitals), as a sign that they are God's people. When you entered to become Kristus' people, you were also ‘circumcised’. What it means is like this: this circumcision was not about slicing off skin from the body, but about Kristus slicing off/out the evil things/issues from our-inc insides. That is, evil things which we like to do because we are human.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In whom also you were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In whom also you were circumcised by a circumcision made without hands, in the putting off of the body of flesh, in the circumcision of Christ,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Lod'o ra sarani miu pake èi, èèna nuka sèmi padhane miu, sama-sama dènge Kristus. Hèia miu abhu mamuri dhu hiu, sèmi Nèngu unu mamuri hiu kahèi. Miu abhu sèmi èèna, lula miu parcaya, peka na, Ama Lamatua pake koasa Na dhu kapai aae èèna, ho pamamuri hari Yesus Kristus nèti mamadhe Na. Lamatua pake kahèi koasa ne'e ho sab'a ètu d'ara miu.<bt>When they *baptised you-pl using water, that was like you were buried together with Kristus. So/and/then you got new life, just like He also got2 new life. You got it like that, because you believed that God used His great power/authority, to bring Yesus Kristus back to life from His death. He also uses that power to work in your insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and buried with him in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and buried with him in baptism, in which you are raised with him through faith in the working of God, who raised him from the dead.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 6:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Uru èèna, miu nuka sèmi dhèu dhu madhe le, lula miu dhu tao sasala rupa-rupa, aa miu dhae j'aj'i mèka dhèu unu Ama Lamatua. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Na saku eele aa'i-aa'i sasala-sasigo miu, aa bagi hia miu mamuri hiu, sama sèmi Na pamamuri hari Yesus Kristus.<bt>Formerly, you were as if you a person who had already died, because you did various *wrongs, and you had not yet become God's people. Even that being the case, nevertheless He wiped away all your wrongs (doublet), and gave new life to you, just like He brought Yesus Kristus back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraptwmais: trespass, false step, transgression, sin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">paraptwmais: trespass, false step, transgression, sin akrobustia: uncircumcision [alienation from God]<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>suzwopoiew: make alive together [same time? / jalike?] xarizomai: forgive, pardon, remit "hemo da shame fo ...?" "take away da shame fo ...?" "let you guys go fo ...?"<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: And you, being dead in trespasses and the uncircumcision of your flesh, he made you alive together with him, having forgiven us all our trespasses,</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 2:1-8</note><v n="14" />Dhu mola-mola ka, èdhi hud'i abhu ku huku, lula èdhi sisu le atora-atora Ama Lamatua. Te ngaa Na saku eele le hahuku se'e ropa ra paku Yesus Kristus ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha.<bt>The correct thing, would be that we-inc should be punished, because we have transgressed God's regulations. But He has wiped away our punishments, when they nailed Kristus on the *cross. [TRANS: depersonified, original put in footnote.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eksaleiphw: remove, destroy, obliterate, rubbing off"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">eksaleiphw: remove, destroy, obliterate, rubbing off xeirographon: document, indictment, hand-written certificate, certificate of indebtedness, bond<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>dogma: decree, proclamation, decision, ordinance, legal demand, legal requirement hupenantios: opposed, against, contrary<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>airw: set aside, take away, remove mesos: the middle<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>proselow: to nail firmly LITERALLY: having removed the legal indictment that stood against us, which was opposed to us, he set it aside, nailing it to the cross;<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Te ngaa Nèngu saku eele le hahuku èdhi sèra, lula Na paku nare le ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha Kristus.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yunani language writes, saying, “But He has wiped away our punishments, because He has nailed (them) to Kristus' cross.”</bt></note><note reference="2:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 2:15</note><v n="15" />Ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha ne, Na segi aa'i le koasa maroga, aa aa'i-aa'i dhu paredha dènge bhabhelu. Ka Na pamakae si ètu madha dhèu ae-ae. Aa'i-aa'i se, nuka sèmi sordad'u dhu segi musu, dhu lèpa kako palème rae dènge lii sod'a, sèna ka pad'elo sasegi ra aa pamakae musu ra.<bt>On that cross, He has beaten (caused to lose/had victory) the powers of darkness, and every(one/thing) that is governing/ruling evilly. So He has shamed them before many people (=in public). That is like a soldier/army which is victorious in battle/war, who comes home and has walks around the village/town with songs, to show/display their victory and shame their enemies.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apekduomai: disarm, spoiled, strip of ruling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">apekduomai: disarm, spoiled, strip of ruling power, strip of arms arxe: ruler<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>eksousia: power deigmatizw: make an example of, mock, expose<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>parresia: openly, boldly, with confidence thriambeuw: lead someone in a triumphal procession<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: He disarmed the rulers and powers, and made a public example, triumphing over them in him/it [Christ/the cross/the victory procession].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu neo pamanahu miu, nèti j'ara-j'ara ta'a-tinu, mage mi pusi-pahae si. Aa ladhe dhèu neo tao lii dènge miu, nèti j'ara-j'ara lod'o be'a, do tao pesta hèru hiu, do atora lod'o ae sasab'a, na, baku pusi-pahae si.<bt>If people want to bring us down concerning regulations of eating-drinking, don't be concerned with/care about/pay attention to them. And if people want to make disputes/issues with you concerning holidays, or new moon feasts, or regulations about the days of rest, don't attend to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krinw: judge brwsis: eating, food|i(16) (16)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">krinw: judge brwsis: eating, food<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>posis: drinking, drink meros: in part<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>heorte: festival, feast neomenia: new moon festival<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>sabbaton: rest day LITERALLY: Therefore let no one judge you in matters of food and drink, a festival or a new moon, or a sabbath,<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 14:1-6</note><v n="17" />J'ara sèmi sèra sa, guna boe! Te sèra sa nuka sèmi mamaho di, dhu èèna na ele. Te ngaa Kristus ne ka dhu asli. Nèngu ne ele boe aa taa-taa.<bt>Matters of those sorts have no use! Cuz (elaboration) they are only like shadows, which will disappear. But Kristus is the original/substance. He is the one who never ever disappears. [NOTE: From consultant check and UNS responses, changed to explicate grounds of comparison.] [CHECK UNS: taa-taa.] [Don't undo Marge's work on the fly.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taa-taa = forever, continually, [UNSs (Dhao"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">taa-taa = forever, continually, [UNSs (Dhao &amp; Kupang) not familiar with it, but doesn't add or lose much here, so concession to the team]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skia: shadow swma: body, [subtance, reality]|i(17)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">skia: shadow swma: body, [subtance, reality]<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: These are a shadow of what is to come, but the substance is of Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ladhe dhèu neo pamanahu miu, lula miu mo'o boe madhutu atora dhu rèngu tao unu ra, baku nanene si. Te ladhe miu nanene si, miu bisa heka abhu j'ara-j'ara hua iia dhu Ama Lamatua neo hia miu. De mage-mage! Te mema abhu dhèu dhu d'èi tenge j'ara ho pamanahu miu. Dad'èi ra, ladhe miu pahaha iisi miu, aa sogo-tagu ana pajuu Lamatua ètu sorga, lula ra pangee, na, abhu tanila dhu peka sèmi èèna. Rèngu tao iisi ra be'a risi nèti dhèu leo aa'i-aa'i ra. Madhutu iia-iia na, sèmi boe èèna. Te ngangee ra sama sèmi dhèu rai-haha biasa di.<bt>[Following Hawaii] If people want to bring you down, because you do not follow/obey regulations which they have made/created themselves, don't listen to them. Cuz (elaboration), if you listen to them, you will not be able to receive the various good things that God wants to give you. So (consequently) be careful! Cuz (elaboration) there really are people who like to find ways to bring you down. They want for you to have to lower/humble/humiliate yourselves, and traditional-worship the *angels, because they think they had a vision which told them (to do) that. They consider themselves to be better than other people. When in fact, that is not the case! Cuz (elaboration) their thinking is merely like that of normal humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="biasa = iia di [tema doesn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">biasa = iia di [tema doesn't work here]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anggelos: angel eike: without cause, fo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">anggelos: angel eike: without cause, fo no reason<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>embateuw: enter into, investigate closely thelon: willing, voluntarily<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>threskeia: religion, worship, religious service, cult, external rites katabrabeuw: condemn, disqualify<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>kenembateuw: make a misstep nous: the mind<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>horaw: see, have a vision tapeinophrosune: humility, modesty, false humility<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>phusiow: blow up, puff up, inflate LITERALLY: Let no one disqualify you, by voluntary [/false] humility and worship of angels, entering into things which he has seen, puffed up for no reason by a sensuous mind,<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kristus èèna Kètu, te ngaa rèngu ro'o boe pa'èki dènge Ne. Aa dhèu unu Kristus, nuka sèmi ngi'u Na dhu Na ator si. Na tao dhèu unu Na asa tabha èra, pake koasa Ama Lamatua. Dènge j'ara ne'e, rèngu j'aj'i nuka sèmi kalua dènge rui dhu pa'èki pa'èra-èra, sèna ka èci bara èci, toke ngi'u dhu kateme bisa sab'a dènge be'a.<bt>Kristus is Head, but they do not want to be bound/linked with Him. And Kristus' people are like His body which He organises/regulates/controls. He makes His people to be increasingly strong/influential, using God's power. In that way, they are like tendons and bones which are strongly connected to each other to mutually help one another, to the point that the entire body can work well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bara = bantu UNSs not know,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">bara = bantu UNSs not know, prefer bantu to soru-bara ; kaj'èpe = malengket ; pakèpa = bapegang ; patuhu = linked end to end (doesn't work for bones and sinews</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="auxanw: to grow auxeesis: cause growth|i(19)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">auxanw: to grow auxeesis: cause growth<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>haphe: joint, connection sundesmos: bond, sinew, ligament<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>epixoregew: to support sumbibazw: unite, bring together<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>kratew: hold fast to something or someone kephalee: head<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: and not holding fast to the head, from whom the body, supported and brought together through its joints and ligaments, grows with a growth that is from God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 4:16</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ladhe èdhi pa'èki dènge Kristus, èdhi unu mamuri hiu<bt>If we are bound with Kristus, we get new life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Miu madhe le sama-sama dènge Kristus. Hèia miu pa'èki heka dènge koasa-koasa maroga ètu rai-haha ne. De nga tao ka miu loe boe madhutu rupa-rupa atora rai-haha? Rèngu peka sèmi ne'e ka:<bt>You have died together with Kristus. So you are no longer bound to the various powers of darkness in this world. So (consequently), why (the hell) are you not ceasing to follow the various regulations/principles of the world? [Over-all construction implies anger or frustration, strong chiding] They say like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apothneskw: die dogmatizw: submit to rules|i(20)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">apothneskw: die dogmatizw: submit to rules<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>stoixeion: fundamental principles, basic spirits [see 2:8] LITERALLY: If you died with Christ to the basic principles of the world, why do you live as if you still belonged to the world and submit to them,<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />&lt;&lt;Mage kèpe ne'e; baku mi'e èèna, mage goi ne'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>“Don't hold this; don't eat that; don't touch/feel this.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haptw: touch, handle, take hold of,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">haptw: touch, handle, take hold of, hold geuomai: taste, eat<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>thiganw: touch LITERALLY: "Do not handle, do not taste, do not touch,"<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Te ngaa atora sèra, dhoka pa'ue-ai nèti dhèu rai-haha, ho ra aj'a mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i. Madhutu iia-iia na, atora sèra dhodhoka uri j'ara-j'ara dhu èèna na ele iia d'ara di!<bt>But those regulations are only made by humans, for them to teach everyone. When in fact those regulations only manage/regulate/deal with matters which will later disappear!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="uri = ator [both used]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">uri = ator [both used]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="entalma: commandment phthora: ruin, destruction, dissolution,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">entalma: commandment phthora: ruin, destruction, dissolution, deterioration, corruption<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>apoxresis: consume, use up LITERALLY: referring to things which are all destroyed as they are used, according to rules and teachings of human beings?<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ladhe sèmi dhèu bisa tao madhutu atora sèra, ra pangee, na, bèli-camèd'a dhèu pakab'ua si, aa peka na, rèngu se d'èlu-mèu titu kèna; dhèu dhu tao iisi ra sèmi dhèu kèpe pa'èra atora agama; dhèu dhu d'ara mako; dhèu dhu paj'èra ngi'u unu ra, dènge dhèu dhu maj'èni sogo-tagu. Madhutu iia-iia na, aad'o! Atora sèra bisa boe pamèu ngangee dhèu rai-haha, dènge d'ara dhu d'èi ad'u-ue bhabhelu!<bt>If it were the case [hypothetical] that someone (actually) could do according to those regulations, they think that people will respect/honour them, and consider them really clever/wise, people who are hold strongly to religious regulations, people who are humble/kind/meek, people who abuse their own bodies, and people who are heavily involved in traditional-worship (excessively diligent at it). When in actual fact, that is not the case! Those regulations cannot cleanse/fix/purify humans' thoughts and thier insides that desire to do evil!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apheidia: severe treatment, severity, rigor ethelothreskia:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">apheidia: severe treatment, severity, rigor ethelothreskia: self-made religion, self-imposed worship, voluntary devotion<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>plesmone: satisfaction, gratification, indulgence tapeinophrosune: humility, modesty, self-abasement, [false humility]<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>time: honor, value LITERALLY: These indeed have the appearance of wisdom, in rigor of worship, self-abasement, severity to the body, but are of no value in checking the indulgence of the flesh.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Ama Lamatua hia le miu mamuri hiu, nuka sèmi Nèngu pamamuri hari miu sama-sama dènge Kristus. Limuri ne, Kristus madhèdi le ètu era dhu kab'ua risi ètu baboa g'ana Ama Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, miu hud'i pangee dhoka j'ara-j'ara dhu pakarej'e d'ara Lamatua.<bt>God has given you new life, just like He has brought you back to life together with Kristus. Now, Kristus is sitting in the most respected place at God's right side. That is why you must think (intentionally) about things/matters/issues that please God2's insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunegeirw: rise up with, be raised,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">sunegeirw: rise up with, be raised, resurrect. Like Romans 6:8 syzeesomen. zetew: seek, look for, desire to possess something<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>anw: above kathemai: sit<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>deksios: right side, right hand LITERALLY: Since therefore you have been raised with Christ, seek the things that are above, where Christ is seated at the right side of God;<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 110:1</note><v n="2" />Pangee dhoka j'ara-j'ara dhu Lamatua d'èi. Baku pusi-pahae dènge j'ara dhu dhodhoka pakarej'e d'ara dhèu rai-haha di.<bt>Keep thinking only about things/matters/issues that God2 likes. Don't be concerned about things that merely please the insides of humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phronew: set one's mind on, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">phronew: set one's mind on, be intent on, think about, ponder, concentrate on LITERALLY: set your minds on the things that are above, not on the things that are on the earth;<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te miu madhe kahèi, ropa Kristus madhe. Hèia mamuri hiu miu èèna kalau boe, lula miu pa'èki le dènge Kristus, dhu bera-bera dènge Ama Lamatua ètu sorga.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you also died when Kristus died. So that new life of yours, is secure/safe (lit. is not shaken), because (you) are bound/linked with Kristus, who is together with God in heaven. [EXEG: Gk /kekruptai/ as ‘kept safe’, not ‘hidden’, see LN 21.12]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apothneskw: die zwe: life|i(3) (3) |rkruptw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">apothneskw: die zwe: life<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>kruptw: hide, conceal, cover, safe, secure/ unseen, invisible, out of sight, (spiritual) LITERALLY: for you died, and your life has been hidden with Christ in God.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Kristus mamuri ètu d'ara miu, aa Na pabe'a mamuri miu. Bèli-camèd'a, ropa Na lèpa hari mai, miu cèu palere-lere dènge Ne kahèi ètu d'ara dadedha dènge kapai Na!<bt>[Following Hawaii] Kristus is living inside you-pl, and He has also made you truly live. Later, when He comes back, you will also appear together with Him in His great high-ness/glory!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cèu = appear, muncul [1 UNS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">cèu = appear, muncul [1 UNS felt didn't work for humans, but others gave several examples where it is used in that way]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phanerow: appear, show, reveal, come doksa:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">phanerow: appear, show, reveal, come doksa: glory, brightness, splendor, radiance<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: When Christ appears, who is our life, then you also will appear with him in glory.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mamuri rupa dhui, aa mamuri rupa hiu<bt>The old model/pattern of life, and the new model of life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Nèti èèna ka, miu hud'i pèci eele ku dad'èi d'ara dhu neo tao bhabhelu-katub'a. Nuka sèmi: d'ara d'èi tao j'ara karehe dènge dhèu dhu j'aj'i boe dhèu èmu-kamali èu; d'ara d'èi tao j'ara-j'ara kaj'alu; d'ara d'èi dhu neo tao madhutu dad'èi d'ara di; d'ara d'èi tao bhabhelu rupa-rupa, aa manga'a dhu d'èi dhoka aa'i-aa'i j'aj'i unu èu di (madhutu iia-iia na, sèra sa nuka sèmi èu sogo-tagu, lula èu ded'e padedha-dedha j'ara leo dhu seti eele Lamatua).<bt>That is why you-pl must get rid of your desires/ tendencies to do evil (doublet). For example: the desire to do evil with someone who is not your-sg spouse; the desire to do filthy/defiling things; the desire to just follow along with your inner passions/desires; the desire to do various sorts of evil; and selfishness/greediness which only wants everything to just be yours-sg (when in fact, that is the same as you being involved in traditional-worship, cuz (elaboration) you are elevating other things which elbow God2 out of the way).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nekrow: put to death melos: member,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">nekrow: put to death melos: member, part, limb<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>porneia: prostitution, fornication, any kind of sexual immorality akatharsia: impurity, uncleanness, dirt, immorality, viciousness<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pathos: passion, sexual passion epithumia: desire, longing, desire for something forbidden<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>kakos: bad, evil pleoneksia: greediness, covetousnesss, a desire to have more<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>eidwlolatria: idolatry, worship of idols LITERALLY: Therefore, put to death what is earthly in you: immorality, impurity, passion, evil desire, and the desire to have more, which is idolatry,<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />J'ara se'e se ka dhu tao Ama Lamatua nasa titu kèna, toke Na neo huku dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu ro'o boe nanene Ne.<bt>Those issues are ones that make God extremely angry, to the point that He wants to punish all people who do not want to listen to/obey Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orge: wrath, anger, indignation, (judgment) apeitheia:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">orge: wrath, anger, indignation, (judgment) apeitheia: disobedience<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: because of which the wrath of God is coming on the sons of disobedience;</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Uru èèna, miu mamuri sèmi èèna ka, lula d'ara miu pa'èki dènge j'ara bhelu sèra.<bt>Previously, you also lived like that, because your insides were bound by those sorts of evil issues.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peripatew: walk around, live, conduct oneself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">peripatew: walk around, live, conduct oneself zaw: live, conduct of life<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: in which you also once walked when you lived in them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Te ngaa limuri ne, miu hud'i pèci eele ku dad'èi d'ara dhu neo ad'u-ue bhabhelu aa'i-aa'i. Nuka sèmi: d'èi nasa; d'ara pana-mag'oro; tèka d'ara dènge dhèu; padhai lii pa'ele iie kolongara dhèu; dènge padhai lii kaj'alu.<bt>But now, you must throw away all of your desires to do evil. For example: easily angered, excessive anger (Idiom: hot insides), resentment, speaking to damage people's good name/reputation; and dirty mouth (=filthy speech).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="udhi = balas dendam ; hèb'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">udhi = balas dendam ; hèb'a ore = talk thoughtlessly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apotithemi: put away, lay aside orge:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">apotithemi: put away, lay aside orge: wrath, anger, indignation,<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>thumos: anger, wrath, rage kakia: malice, badness, morally faulty, ill-will, wickedness, malicious gossip, desire to injure someone<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>blasphemia: slander, defamation of character, blasphemy aisxrologia: evil speech, obscene talk, abusive speech<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: But now, you also put away all anger, wrath, malice, slander, foul talk from your mouth;</Message></Annotation><v n="9-10" />Aa miu èci dènge èci baku kapod'e-kabèli. Lula miu core eele le dad'èi d'ara dhu neo tao bhelu, aa tèke eele j'ara mamuri dhui sèra.<bt>And each of you should not be deceiving/lying/ conning/cheating each other. Because you have gotten rid of your insides that desire to do evil, and have left behind/abandoned your old way of life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pseudomai: lie apekduomai: take off, put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">pseudomai: lie apekduomai: take off, put off<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>palaios: old praksis: practice, deed, action, activity<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: do not lie to each other, because you have taken off the old nature with its practices,</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 4:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Aa limuri ne, miu gati dènge d'ara dhu hiu. Èèna nuka sèmi dhèu core eele le mèdha-papake dhui dhu kaj'alu, sèna ka silu mèdha hiu dhu mèu. Ama Lamatua ka dhu paj'aj'i miu. Aa limuri ne, Na tao miu asa tadhe pabe'a-be'a Nèngu, aa tao miu j'aj'i ca ropa dènge Ne.<bt>And now you have replaced it, with a new insides. That is like a person taking off/getting rid of his old filthy clothes/shirt, to change use/wear clean new clothes. God is the one who created you. And now He also makes you increasingly understand Him more deeply, and makes you to become the same model/type as Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="silu = pake ; hera ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">silu = pake ; hera = kaj'alu, kotor</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enduw: put on, get dressed neos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">enduw: put on, get dressed neos: new<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>anakainow: renew, make new epignwsis: knowledge<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>eikwn: form, image, likeness LITERALLY: and have put on the new nature, which is being renewed in knowledge according to the image of its creator,<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 1:26, Epesus 4:24</note><v n="11" />Ètu d'ara mamuri hiu ne, èdhi hag'e boe, na, rèngu sèra dhèu Yahudi, do dhèu Yahudi boe; dhèu dhu madhutu suna, do dhèu dhu suna boe; dhèu leo rai kara, do dhèu dhu ad'a aad'o;<bt>In this new life, we-inc do not distinguish people, saying, they are Yahudi people, or not Yahudi people; people who have participated in circumcision, or people who have not been circumcised; foreigners/strangers, or ill-mannered/uncivilised;</bt><note reference="3:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ètu d'ara Alkitab lii Yunani, peka na, &lt;&lt;dhèu Barbar dènge dhèu Skutia&gt;&gt;. Ra peka, dhèu Barbar se, dhèu leo rae kara dhu pea ètu li'u koasa paredha Roma. Aa ra cap dhèu Skutia sèra, dhèu dènge boe ad'a.<bt>The Yunani language Bible, writes, saying, “Barbar people and Skutia people”. They say Barbar people are foreigners outside the authority of the Roma government. And they branded Skutia people, as ill-mannered/uncivilised people.</bt></note>dhèu ènu, do ènu boe. Se'e se kolo-karisi na, aad'o! Te ngaa dhu lèke ka, ladhe rèngu pa'èki dènge Kristus, aa Nèngu mamuri ètu d'ara ra.<bt>slaves, or non-slaves. It is not those things that are important! But what is right/true, is if/whether they are bound with Kristus, and whether He is living in their insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Here there cannot be Greek"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Here there cannot be Greek and Jew, circumcised and uncircumcised, barbarian, Scythian, slave, free man, but Christ is all, and in all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ama Lamatua hag'e nare le miu, lula Na sue miu. Dad'èi Na sèna ka miu j'aj'i dhèu mola-mèci Na dhu leko-leo nèti dhèu rai-haha leo sèra. Nèti èèna ka, miu hud'i j'aj'i ku dhèu d'ara hua iia, d'ara be'a, pahaha iisi, lii mako, dènge taha mere d'ara.<bt>God has chosen you, because He loves/pities you. His purpose/intention is for you to be/become His clean/pure/holy people who are different from other humans. That is why you must be/become people who have noble insides (gentle, kind), good livers (kind, generous, gracious), lower yourselves (humble), polite words, and patient insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="splagxon: inward parts oiktirmos: pity, mercy,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">splagxon: inward parts oiktirmos: pity, mercy, compassion<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>xrestotes: goodness, kindness, generosity, desire for another's good tapeinophrosune: humility, humbleness, lowliness, modesty<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>prautes: gentleness, meekness, humility, courtesy, consideration makrothumia: longsuffering, patience, forbearance<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: Put on then, as God's chosen ones, holy and beloved, compassion, kindness, lowliness, meekness, patience,</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Miu hud'i taha mere d'ara, aa èci tadhe mèu èci. Ladhe nèti miu, abhu dhu tenge lii langu dènge angalai na, na, baku tèka d'ara dènge ne. Te ngaa miu hud'i pabhèlu eele sasala na, aa abho ne, nuka sèmi Lamatua dhu pabhèlu eele le sasala miu.<bt>You must be patient and understanding with each other. If there are those among you who are (trying to) create issues/disputes with his companions/fellows, don't build resentment. But you must (completely) forget about his wrong [addressing the heart], and grant forgiveness to him [addressing the social action], just like God2 has completely forgotten about your-pl wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="abho = ampon [UNSs prefer latter]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">abho = ampon [UNSs prefer latter]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anexw: put up with, endure, bear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">anexw: put up with, endure, bear with, forbear xarizw: forgive, give freely. "hemo da shame from you?" "hemo da bad kine stuff from you?" "take away da shame?" "throw out da shame?" "let you guys go?" In this context of interpersonal relationships, "let um go" fits best, and it is all right if the same thing is attributed to God without adding all the details.<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>momphe: complaint, grievance, blame LITERALLY: bearing with others and forgiving each other, if anyone has a complaint against another; just as the Lord has also forgiven you, you also do the same;<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 4:2,32</note><v n="14" />Sanèd'e, ee. Te sasue èèna risi aa'i nèti ngaa-ngaa. De miu hud'i pake sasue ne ètu d'ara miu, nuka sèmi mèdha-papake ètu ua. Te sasue èèna, nuka sèmi loa hèngu dhu èdhi manènu, sèna ka j'aj'i sig'i dhu saraga titu kèna. Ne'e ne ka dhu pa'èki èdhi j'aj'i mi èci.<bt>Remember ee, cuz (elaboration) that love is more important than everything. So (consequently) you must wear love in/on your insides, just like people wear clothes on their bodies. Cuz (elaboration) that love (that I'm talking about), is like a thread which we-inc weave into a fine/beautiful piece of cloth. That is what binds/ties us together into one.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agape: love, intelligent and purposeful self-giving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">agape: love, intelligent and purposeful self-giving sundesmos: bond, bond that unites<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>teleiotes: perfection, maturity, completeness LITERALLY: and above all these, love, which binds everything together in perfection.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Èdhi bisa padame dènge Ama Lamatua, lula Kristus. De miu hud'i soro tèke kahèi dadame Kristus ne, uri d'ara miu. Te Lamatua d'èi ka, miu aa'i-aa'i mi mamuri mera-milu èci dènge èci, lula miu pa'èki j'aj'i ngi'u èci. Aa d'ara miu hud'i me'a manèngi makasi, lula Lamatua unu Na ka hag'e nare miu.<bt>We can have peace/reconciliation with God, because of Kristus. So (consequently), you must also allow that peace of Kristus to arrange/regulate/control your insides. Cuz (elaboration) God2 wants for you all to live in situational and relational peace (doublet) with each other, because you are all bound/tied/joined together as one body. And your insides must also be continually grateful, because God2 himself is the one who has chosen you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eirene: peace, inner peace (attitude of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">eirene: peace, inner peace (attitude of mind), tranquility, condition of rest, contentment brabeuw: rule, decide, control, judge, govern<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>kalew: call, summon, invite swma: body<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>euxaristos: thankful, grateful LITERALLY: Let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, to which you were called in one body, and be thankful.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Hud'i laa Lii Holo-Nori Kristus uri d'ara miu dènge mamuri miu kahèi. Lii Holo-Nori se'e, nuka sèmi mèdha-panyau dhu kab'ua, dhu Na pangèd'u mi miu. Lii se'e pad'elo j'ara ho miu bisa me'a madha j'ara ae-ae, madhutu ngangee Lamatua. Ka miu bisa pake Lii se'e, sèna ka aj'a-nori, aa pasanèd'e miu èci dènge èci. Ladhe nori dhèu-dhèu miu, mage dènge sakaa, te ngaa pake lii dènge d'ara dhu taleo moro-moro dhu pènu dènge rasa makasi. Pake lii sod'a koa-kio, lii sod'a dhu miu abhu nèti Roh Mola-Mèci Lamatua, aa lii sod'a dhu miu mesa mi suri ho koa-kio Ama Lamatua.<bt>Let Kristus' Words/Sayings/Message also arrange/regulate/control your insides and your lives. Those Words are like expensive/valuable possessions which He has given you. They show the way for you to be able to understand many things, in accord with God2's thinking. So you can use these Words to teach (doublet) and remind/warn each other. If/when you teach them to your people, don't teach with roughness/rudeness/abusive, but use words and insides that are wide (=gracious/generous) and which is full of a sense of gratitude [deliberately trying to leave open toward God &amp; other people]. Use praise songs, songs that you get/receive from God2's Holy Spirit, and songs that you yourselves have written/composed to praises (doublet) God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taleo moro-moro = luas sekali"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">taleo moro-moro = luas sekali</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enoikew: live, dwell, be at home,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">enoikew: live, dwell, be at home, stay plousiws: richly, abundantly, in all its wealth of meaning and power, with its wide application to every sphere of life and experience<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>nouthetew: admonish, warn against error, instruct, stimulate, encourage, urge to forsake evil psalmos: psalm, song of praise, poems which are sung<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>humvos: hymn, song, praise to God wde: song, sacred song, any song<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>pneumatikos: spiritual, sung in the Spirit, voicing holy aspirations xaris: favor, grace, gift, thankfulness, gratitude<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>adw: sing LITERALLY: Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly in all wisdom, as you teach and admonish one another with psalms, hymns, spiritual songs, singing with thankfulness in your hearts to God;<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Miu j'aj'i le ai g'ana nèti Yesus Kristus. De sanèd'e, te aa'i-aa'i dhu miu padhue-padhai sèra, mèti kolongara Lamatua. Aa aa'i-aa'i dhu miu tao sèra mèti kolongara Lamatua kahèi. De baku bhèlu tao aa'i-aa'i dènge kolongara Kètu miu, Yesus Kristus. Aa manèngi makasi taruu mi Ama Na, Ama Lamatua.<bt>You have already become Yesus Kristus' representatives/right hand. So (consequently) remember that everything that you say, is bearing God2's name/reputation. And everything that you do, is also bearing His name/reputation. [Deliberately kept separate.] So (consequently), do not forget to do everything with the name/reputation of your Head, Yesus Kristus. And give thanks continually to His Father, God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And all things, whatever you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And all things, whatever you do, in word or in action, do everything in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16-17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 5:19-20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mamuri dhèu Kristen èci dènge èci hud'i sèmi ngaa sa?<bt>How should Kristen people live with each other?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Bhèni dhu dènge dhèu èmu! Miu hud'i mamuri nanene ku dhèu èmu miu, lula èèna ka dhu lèke mi dhèu-dhèu dhu madhutu Yesus Kristus.<bt>Wives! You-pl must listen/obey your spouses, because that is appropriate for people who follow/obey Yesus Kristus. [NOTE: this is the same construction the team are using in Ef. 5]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupotassw: submit, be subject, subject yourself,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">hupotassw: submit, be subject, subject yourself, subordinate yourself, obey, be obedient, give way to, adapt yourself to, place yourself under anekw: be proper, fitting, appropriate<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: Wives, be subject to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 5:22, 1 Petrus 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Mone dhu dènge dhèu èmu! Miu hud'i sue ku dhèu èmu miu, aa baku sakaa dènge ne, ka papèd'a d'ara na.<bt>Husbands! You must love/pity your spouses, and not be harsh/oppressing her, so that (you) make her angry/resentful.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agapaw: love, active and unceasing care"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">agapaw: love, active and unceasing care for her well-being pikrainw: become bitter, be harsh to. "Make any kine" includes this, but doesn't highlight the husband's bad attitude as much pikrainein does.<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: Husbands, keep on loving your wives and do not be harsh to them.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 5:25, 1 Petrus 3:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ana-ana aa'i-aa'i! Miu hud'i nanene ina-ama miu, ètu madha j'ara aa'i-aa'i ra, te èèna ka dhu pakarej'e d'ara Ama Lamatua.<bt>Children! You must listen/obey your parents in every issue/matter, cuz (elaboration) that is what pleases God2's insides. [NLT, CEV, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupakouw: obey, listen to, follow, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">hupakouw: obey, listen to, follow, be subject to euarestos: pleasing, acceptable<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: Children, obey your parents in everything, for this pleases the Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 6:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ina-ama aa'i-aa'i! Miu baku ènyi aa lii taka leli mi ana-ana miu, te aad'o na, ra nasa ka ra parui. Mage-mage d'ara ra ta'u'a dènge miu.<bt>Parents! Don't oppressing/pressing and speaking harshly without cause/thought to your children, so that they become angry and react. [NOTE: GK to here same as Ef. 6] May it not be that they (one word) can't wait to get out of the relationship with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta u'a = tawar hati, feel"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">ta u'a = tawar hati, feel no obligation to the relationship</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Baku sakaa dènge ana-ana, sèna ka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">Baku sakaa dènge ana-ana, sèna ka dara ra baku ta u'a dènge miu.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="erethizw: provoke to anger, embitter, exasperate,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">erethizw: provoke to anger, embitter, exasperate, drive to resentment, irritate, arouse athumew: lose heart, discourage<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERALLY: Parents, do not provoke your children to anger, so that they may not become discouraged.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 6:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dhèu sab'a sèra! Ètu rai-haha ne miu hud'i tao ku madhutu dad'èi lamatua miu ètu d'ara sasab'a aa'i-aa'i ra. Mage dhoka mere d'ara di, lod'o dhu lamatua miu ètu madha miu. Te ngaa tenge la j'ara, ho pakarej'e taruu d'ara ra. Sab'a dènge be'a, lula miu dhu me'a, na, Ama Lamatua dhu ladhe patae miu.<bt>Workers! In this world, you must follow/obey your bosses/masters in all matters. Don't just keep currying favour while your masters are still with you. But make the effort so that you are always making them happy. Do all your work well/correctly, because you know that God is checking up on you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ladhe patae = seksama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">ladhe patae = seksama</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupakouw: obey, listen to ophthalmodoulia: eye"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">hupakouw: obey, listen to ophthalmodoulia: eye service, work for appearances, work for show, service performed to attract attention<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>anthrwpareskos: men pleaser, looking for people's approval haplotes: sincerity, simplicity, singleness, uprightness, frankness<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>phobow: to fear, have respect for, have reverence for LITERALLY: Slaves, obey in everything your earthly masters, not with eyeservice, as menpleasers, but in singleness of heart, fearing the Lord.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23-24" />Miu sad'i sab'a ngaa èèna ka, na, sab'a la mola-mola. Miu hud'i sab'a sasab'a miu dènge d'ara kateme hia lamatua miu ètu rai-haha ne, nuka sèmi miu sab'a hia Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. De miu lalau-lalo'o Ne, te Nèngu ka dhu b'ala rui-j'aj'èra miu, dènge hia miu pusaka.<bt>[CHECK /lalau-lalo'o/ in this context. ALT: /sab'e hia Ne/] Whatever you are doing, do it correctly. with You must work wholeheartedly for your human boss/master as if you are working for your Head, Yesus Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) you are working for Him. And He will be the one who will repay/reciprocate your reward/payment/wages and give you your inheritance.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaseha = sewa ; lalau-lalo'o ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">kaseha = sewa ; lalau-lalo'o = serve, see to the needs of (but Michael feels it only works for higher-lower, not lower-higher, e.g. mother to children, etc. but not servant to master, sort of like urus) ; haha'u = layani, perhatikan kebutuhan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Miu hud'i sab'e nuka sèmi miu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">Miu hud'i sab'e nuka sèmi miu sab'a hia Kètu miu Yesus Kristus, te sab'a boe hia mi dhèu rai-haha.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ek psuxes: heartily, with all your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">ek psuxes: heartily, with all your heart, put your whole heart into it, from the soul, eagerly, zestfully LITERALLY: Whatever you do, work heartily for the Lord and not for people,<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>apolambanw: receive antapodosis: repaying, reward<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>kleronomia: inheritance, (eternal life) LITERALLY: because you know that you will receive the inheritance from the Lord as the reward. You serve the Lord Christ.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Te ngaa ladhe miu sab'a lèke boe j'ara, bèli-camèd'a Na huku miu. Lula Nèngu èèna dhu bia boe cabèka, aa ladhe boe rèhu dhèu.<bt>But if you do not work correctly/right, He will punish you. Cuz (elaboration) He is just/fair/unbiased, and doesn't play favourites/ biased2 (Idiom: doesn't choose faces).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adikew: do wrong, violate the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">adikew: do wrong, violate the law komizw: carry off, get, receive pay, receive wages, bring<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>proswpolempsia: partiality, favoritism, respect of persons LITERALLY: For the wrongdoer will be paid back for his wrongdoing, and without favoritism.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:22-25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 6:5-8; Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 10:17, Epesus 6:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Miu lamatua sèra! Miu hud'i uri ku dhèu dhu sab'a hia miu sèra dènge mola, aa bia boe cabèka. Sanèd'e ee, te miu dènge Lamatua ètu sorga dhu uri miu kahèi.<bt>Bosses/masters! You must oversee/manage/ organise/regulate your workers/servants correctly and fairly. Remember that you also have a Boss/Master in heaven who oversee/manage/ organise/regulate you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parexw: give, grant something to someone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">parexw: give, grant something to someone isotes: fair, 'fair and square'<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Masters, give your servants that which is just and fair, knowing that you also have a Master in Heaven.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 6:9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii holo-nori<bt>Various advice</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Miu hud'i maj'èni sabaj'a. Aa miu hud'i mase'a ku dènge j'ara-j'ara dhu miu padhai dènge Ama Lamatua, aa manèngi-mangaj'i dhu pènu dènge d'ara makasi.<bt>You-pl must be diligent to keep praying. And (you) must be aware/informed about the things/matters that you speak/discuss with God, and pray using insides which are full of gratitude.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proskarterew: adhere to, persist in, busy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">proskarterew: adhere to, persist in, busy yourself with, be busily engaged in, be devoted to, continue in gregorew: be awake, stay awake, be on the alert, watch, be wide awake about it, be watchful<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: Be devoted to prayer, and stay alert in it with thanksgiving,</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Baku bhèlu sabaj'a hia ji'i, aa manèngi ho Ama Lamatua bhoke j'ara, sèna ka ji'i bisa lole dènge dhèu, j'ara-j'ara dhu uru èèna pahuni lula-nèti Kristus. Sanèd'e, te ja'a ètu d'ara bui ne, lula ja'a padhue-padhai Kristus mi dhèu.<bt>Don't forget to pray for us-exc, and ask that God opens the way for us to be able to tell/explain to people matters which were previously hidden about Kristus. Remember that I am here in prison, because I have been telling people about Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: at the same time, praying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: at the same time, praying also for us, that God may open to us a door for the word, to declare the mystery of Christ, on account of which I have been put in prison,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Sabaj'a sèna ka ja'a bisa lole paled'a Lii Lolo Be'a ne, sèna ka dhèu bisa re'a mèu.<bt>Pray that I can tell/explain that Good News with real clarity, so that people can understand it well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: that I may make it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: that I may make it clear, as I ought to speak.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Mamuri dènge mola ètu talora aae dhèu dhu parcaya mèka Kristus. Pake paie-iie lod'o dhu taleo dhu Ama Lamatua hia miu.<bt>Live right in the midst of people who do not yet believe in Kristus. Use well each opportunity which God gives to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Conduct yourselves wisely toward outsiders,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Conduct yourselves wisely toward outsiders, making the most of the time.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 5:16</note><v n="6" />Ladhe miu padhai lii, padhai dènge lii mako, dhu palèke dènge d'ara dhèu. Mage padhai dhu paroca dhèu. Pake lii-lii dhu lèke, sèna ka miu bisa dhaa hari dènge be'a, ladhe abhu dhèu pakarèi dènge miu.<bt>If/when you speak, speak kindly/sweetly in such a way as to connect with/impact people's insides. Don't speak in ways that bore them. Use words that are true/correct/ appropriate/ connect, so you can be able to respond back well, if there are people who question you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let your speech be always"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let your speech be always with grace, seasoned with salt, that you may know how you ought to answer every person.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus suri pa'èle sasuri na<bt>Paulus closes his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Pe Tikikus dhiu lole dènge miu, j'ara mamuri ja'a. Nèngu ne a'ari pasue èdhi dhu ladhe-leru dhèu-dhèu unu Lamatua dhu ne'a boe roca. Uru èèna, nèngu pakako sasab'a Lamatua sama-sama dènge ja'a kahèi.<bt>Later Tikikus is going to come tell you about my situation/life. He is a sibling whom we-exc love, and serves God2's people with loyalty/without boredom/ giving up. Previously, he also carried out God2's work together with me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Tychicus will make known to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Tychicus will make known to you all the things about me. He is a beloved brother, a faithful helper and fellow servant in the Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 20:4, 2 Timotius 4:12</note><v n="8" />Ja'a pua na dhiu, sèna ka pa'èra d'ara miu, aa lole dènge miu j'ara mamuri ji'i ètu ne'e.<bt>I sent/commissioned him like that, so he would go strengthen/encourage your insides, and narrate to you about us here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have sent him to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have sent him to you for this purpose: that you may know the things about us, and he may encourage your hearts,</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 6:21-22</note><v n="9" />Ja'a pua Onesimus kahèi lèpa palere dènge ne. Onesimus ne a'ari pasue dhu sab'a ne'a boe roca kahèi. Nèngu ne, dhèu miu. Dua ra, pe lole dènge miu j'ara-j'ara dhu j'aj'i le ètu ne'e.<bt>I am also sending home Onesimus, to accompany him. That Onesimus is also a loyal sibling whom we-inc love. He is one of you people. The two of them will narrate to you everything that has happened here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: With Onesimus, a faithful and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: With Onesimus, a faithful and beloved brother, who is from you. They will make known to you all things which have happened here,</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Pilmon 10-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Aristarkus hia lii maho'o kahèi hia miu. Ra taha ne ètu d'ara bui sama-sama dènge ja'a. Markus, a'ari nèti Barnabas, hia lii maho'o kahèi. Uru èèna, ja'a moa mema le dènge miu, na, ladhe Markus dhiu pangad'o dènge miu, na, sèmi mere ne dènge be'a.<bt>Aristarkus sends greetings to you. They are detaining him in prison together with me. Barnabas' sibling/ relative, named Markus, also sends greetings. Previously, I had instructed you beforehand, that if Markus came to see you, receive him well/favourably. [NOTE to daughter translations: Many lgs do not have a generic word for cousin, so you'll have to discuss this. Commentaries are not clear on what the relationship is, but some think Barnabas was the nephew of Mary, who was John Mark's mother. Since we don't know how the link works, we suggest you map the roles. I.e. Barnabas functioned in a “kakak” role, and Mark in an “adik” role.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, greets"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, greets you, and Marcus, Barnabas's sister's son, concerning whom you received orders: if he comes to you, receive him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 19:29, 27:2, Pilmon 24, Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 12:12, 25, 13:13, 15:37-39</note><v n="11" />Yesus, (dhu èdhi pangare ne, &lt;&lt;Yustus&gt;&gt;) hia lii maho'o kahèi mi miu. Nèti angalai aa'i-aa'i dhu sama-sama pakako sasab'a Ama Lamatua, dhoka rèngu tèlu ra se'e ka dhu j'aj'i dhèu sarani nèti suku Yahudi. Aa rèngu se'e ka dhu pa'èra d'ara ja'a.<bt>Yesus (whom we also call “Yustus”) also sends greetings to you. Among all the companions who together carry out the work of God, only those three are ones who have become Kristen people from the Yahudi people. And these are the ones who strengthen/encourage my insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And Jesus, who is called"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And Jesus, who is called Justus. They are from the circumcision [group]. These are my only fellow workers for God's kingdom, who have been a comfort to me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Angalai miu Epapras ètu ne'e, aa na hia miu lii maho'o kahèi. Nèngu ne dhèu sab'a hia Yesus Kristus. Nèngu ne ka dhu loe boe sabaj'a hia miu dènge a'èra na, aa na manèngi sèna ka Ama Lamatua pa'èra dènge tao pamèci miu, aa tao miu j'aj'i me'a mèu dad'èi Na.<bt>Your friend Epafras is here, and he also sends greetings to you. He is a servant/worker of Yesus Kristus. He never ceases to pray with all his might for you, and asks that God will make you strong, make you complete, and make you truly understand His will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Epaphras, who is from you,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Epaphras, who is from you, a servant of Christ, greets you, always laboring fervently for you in prayers, that you may stand mature and fully assured in all the will of God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 1:7, Pilmon 23</note><v n="13" />Ja'a pasanèd'e mema miu, na, Epapras ne, dhu sab'a bia hia miu dènge dhèu-dhèu Kristen ètu kota Laodikia dènge kota Herapolis.<bt>I am reminding you directly that, Epafras had worked very hard (heavily) for you/for your benefit, and for the Kristen people in the city of Laodikia and the city of Herapolis.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I testify of him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I testify of him, that he works hard for you, and those in Laodicea, and those in Hierapolis.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Abhu lii maho'o kahèi nèti Demas dènge dote Lukas dhu èdhi sue.<bt>There are greetings from Demas, and from doctor Lukas, whom we-inc love.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Luke, the beloved physician, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas, greet you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Timotius 4:10, 11, Pilmon 24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ja'a hia lii maho'o mi a'ari dhèu parcaya ètu kota Laodikia. Baku bhèlu hia lii maho'o ja'a mi mama Nimfa dènge dhèu-dhèu parcaya dhu tema pakaboko ètu d'ara èmu na.<bt>I send greetings to the believing siblings who are in the city of Laodikia. Don't forget to pass on my greetings to mama Nimfa and the believers who normally/often gather in her house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Greet the brothers who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Greet the brothers who are in Laodicea, and Nymphas, and the church which is in her house.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Pe, ladhe miu aa'i-aa'i mi ètu kota Kolose baca mere sasuri ne, na, mi pa'adhu hia dhèu-dhèu parcaya ètu kota Laodikia, sèna ka rèngu baca kahèi. Aa miu hud'i baca kahèi sasuri dhu ja'a pa'adhu kèdhi hia rèngu uru sèra.<bt>Later when all of you in Kolose have finished reading this letter, send it on to the believers in the city of Laodikia so that they can also read it. And you must also read the letter that I once/already sent to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And when this letter is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And when this letter is read among you, cause that it be read also in the church of the Laodiceans, and that you also read the letter from Laodicea.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Pasanèd'e Arkipus, peka na, &lt;&lt;Èu baku bhèlu pakako toke pa'èle, sasab'a dhu èu sèmi more nèti Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remind/warn Arkipus, saying, “You-sg must not forget to carry out to completion, that job/responsibility which you received from God2.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And say to Archippus, &quot;Take"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And say to Archippus, "Take heed to the ministry which you have received in the Lord, that you fulfill it."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Pilmon 2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Baku bhèlu, peka na, ra taha ja'a ètu d'ara bui ne era.<bt>Don't forget that they are still detaining me in this prison.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ja'a manèngi sèna ka Ama Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi dedha miu.<bt>I ask that God show His goodness/kindness/grace/favour to you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <span class="Italic">Sasuri ne, ja'a ènyi ai pake kacui-aai ja'a unu ku.</span>
      <bt>
        <span class="Italic">This letter I have signed using my own hand,</span>
      </bt>
      <Annotation class="General" selectedText="ènyi ai = (v) stamp w/fingerprint">
        <Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z">ènyi ai = (v) stamp w/fingerprint or sign</Message>
      </Annotation>
      <Annotation class="General" selectedText="meth' hymoon: a little different from">
        <Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:53:30Z" status="Information">meth' hymoon: a little different from hymiin. LITERALLY: The greeting by the hand of Paul. Remember my bonds. Grace be with you.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message>
      </Annotation>
    </p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <span class="Italic">Salam nèti ja'a,</span>
      <bt>
        <span class="Italic">Greeting/leavetaking from me,</span>
      </bt>
    </p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <span class="Italic">Paulus</span>
      <bt>
        <span class="Italic">Paulus</span>
      </bt>
    </p>
  </book>
</bible>